<section>
  <h2>Framework Philosophy</h2>
  <layout-text>
    <p>Vanilla Breeze follows HTML-first, CSS-second, JavaScript-third principles. This means:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Universal compatibility</strong> - Components work with any backend that generates HTML</li>
      <li><strong>No build step required</strong> - Use directly in the browser for basic usage</li>
      <li><strong>Progressive enhancement</strong> - Content is accessible without JavaScript</li>
      <li><strong>Web Components</strong> - Provide interactivity when needed</li>
    </ol>
    <p>The integrations provide idiomatic components for each framework while maintaining Vanilla Breeze conventions.</p>
  </layout-text>
</section>

